  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Yes I referenced that, but eventually what I needed was this: \nhttps://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/reference.html#searchparameters\n\nAnd from there I could figure out the values for search parameters:\n`idx, fD, dFR` etc. Then from there I can build a query string to pass to the page pretty easily:\n`/?q=mysearchterm&dFR[category][0]=disjunctiveFacet&fR=facet`.\n\nIs there somewhere that defines all the different mapping values you can set?\n\n``` js\nurlSync: {\n  trackedParameters: ['query', 'page', 'attribute:*'],\n  mapping: {\n    p: 'page',\n    q: 'query',\n    fR: 'facetRefinement',\n    dFR: 'disjunctiveFacetRefinement'\n      //what else?\n  }\n}\n\n```\n\nBtw, thanks for all your great help :) \n",
